label: implements
comment: Relationship from a physical network to an abstract cellular network, indicating that the former is part of the latter. Used from an IP network to indicate that it forms the cellular network backbone, and from a radio access network to indicate that it implements a cell in a location.

label: accessFrom
comment: Refers from an access context to the space in which access has or may have taken place.

label: amends
comment: The Process uses and alters the value of an instance of Data, and is not blocked if it cannot access the Data.

label: amends
comment: Relationship between an interactive process user and data they enter, review and update by using the process.

label: appends
comment: The Process creates new instances of Data, adding them to a collection but not overwriting existing instances. This is a type of update operation, but the Process does not need access to previous values.

label: assertedAmendsData
comment: Human-Data relationship added to label cases where a Human-amendsData-Data relationship has been asserted. This is now a deprecated feature of the domain model, so the label is added so it can be used to generate a suitable modelling error.

label: assertedInputsData
comment: Human-Data relationship added to label cases where a Human-inputsData-Data relationship has been asserted. This is now a deprecated feature of the domain model, so the label is added so it can be used to generate a suitable modelling error.

label: assertedViewsData
comment: Human-Data relationship added to label cases where a Human-viewsData-Data relationship has been asserted. This is now a deprecated feature of the domain model, so the label is added so it can be used to generate a suitable modelling error.

label: creates
comment: The Process creates the value of the Data, and does not require access to it after that.

label: enablesUserAccess
comment: Relationship between an interactive process and data, signifying that a user interacts with the data via the process.

label: enablesUserInput
comment: Relationship between an interactive process and data, signifying that a user entes the data via the process.

label: enablesUserOutput
comment: Relationship between an interactive process and data, signifying that a user views the data via the process.

label: enablesUserUpdate
comment: Relationship between an interactive process and data, signifying that a user updates the data via the process.

label: handles
comment: Common base class for interactions between processes and data. Used only in matching patterns that should cover processes that serve or process data.

label: enters
comment: Relationship between an interactive process user and data they enter using the process.

label: interactsWithData
comment: Relationship between an interactive process user and data they interact with using the process. Note that this is not a special case of interactsRemotelyWithData, as that only indicates a potential interaction.

label: isSpam
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate data flows that contain unsolicited messages sent to users, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: noDU
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate Process assets that are not involved in application data processing, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns as appropriate. Note that these processes can still be involved in data exchanges.

label: processes
comment: The base type for relationships signifying that the Process in some way makes use of the Data.

label: reads
comment: The Process uses the Data values without altering them, and is blocked if it cannot access the Data.

label: receives
comment: The Process uses the Data values without altering them, and is not blocked if it cannot access the Data.

label: relays
comment: Link from a process to a data asset indicating that the process acts as a transparent relay for this data.

label: serves
comment: The Process provides access to the Data for other processes, but does not make use of the Data for itself.

label: stores
comment: A copy of the Data is stored on the Host.

label: updates
comment: The Process uses and alters the value of the Data, and is blocked if it cannot access the Data.

label: views
comment: Relationship between an interactive process user and data they view using the process.

label: contains
comment: Relationship between a Pod and a Process running (inside a Container) within that Pod.

label: isContainer
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts in the Container class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isPod
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts in the Pod class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: canGetKeys
comment: An inferred relationship from a Data Access asset to a Data Asset, indicating that the Data Asset is encrypted using keys from a vault, but the Data Access (i.e., the associated Process) can get the keys.

label: canRead
comment: Links a Data Use to a Data Copy that can be read (remotely) by the Data Use.

label: canWrite
comment: Links a Data Use to a Data Copy that can be read (remotely) by the Data Use.

label: copyOf
comment: The DataAsset represents a serialised copy of the Data.

label: crudc
comment: The Process creates the DataCopy stored on its host.

label: crudd
comment: The Process deletes the DataCopy stored on its host.

label: crudr
comment: The Process reads the DataCopy stored on its host.

label: crudu
comment: The Process updates the DataCopy stored on its host.

label: enablesAccess
comment: Relationship to a Data Access (inferred asset) from the Process that makes the Data accessible to Processes.

label: flows
comment: The DataFlow is a flow of the Data.

label: flowsFrom
comment: The DataFlow is from the Process.

label: flowsFromIn
comment: Relationship from a data flow to a space indicating that the data flow can be sent by the source process when in that context.

label: flowsIn
comment: The DataFlow is a flow of the Data to a consumer from a data store.

label: flowsOut
comment: The DataFlow is a flow of the Data from a producer towards a data store.

label: flowsTo
comment: The DataFlow is to the Process.

label: flowsToIn
comment: Relationship from a data flow to a space indicating that the data flow can be received by the destination process when in that context.

label: flowsVia
comment: Relationship from a DataFlow to a DataStep between adjacent processes that forms part of the end to end DataFlow.

label: fromSource
comment: Relationship between Data Access assets, similar to fulfils, except fromSource refers to the original source of data, i.e. the Data Output asset associated with a Process that creates or modifies the Data.

label: fulfils
comment: The DataFlow, DataSet or Data Access and associated Process is the means by which the related Data Access is possible.

label: includesField
comment: Relationship from a Data Copy or Data Flow (a serialized data asset) to DataFields representing their inclusion in the serialized data.

label: noDX
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate Process assets that are not involved in application data exchanges, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns as appropriate. Note that these processes cannot be involved in data processing either.

label: storesCopy
comment: Relationship between a host and a copy of data stored on the host.

label: usedBy
comment: The DataUse represents a use of some data by the Process.

label: usedFor
comment: The DataUse represents a use of the Data by some Process.

label: atHost
comment: Link from a DataPool representing data loaded by a data source or service, and the process host.

label: channelTried
comment: Self-referential relationship marking a data channel as having already been visited by an iterative construction pattern.

label: connectsData
comment: The DataConnection represents an exchange of data to or from the related Process.

label: dataChannelEnd
comment: Link from a DataChannel to a DataAccess asset, indicating the process associated with the DataAsset is the end of the Channel.

label: dataChannelFor
comment: The DataPath represents a chain of process-process communications enabling the use of data represented by the DataUse asset.

label: dataChannelFrom
comment: The DataChannel represents a view of inter-process data transfer in which the related Process is accessing a data source or store.

label: dataChannelTo
comment: The DataChannel represents a view of inter-process data transfer in which the related Process is a data source or store.

label: dataPathEnd
comment: Reference from a Data asset to a Process that is at the end of a constructed DataPath (meaning construction starts from that Process).

label: dataPathFor
comment: The DataPath represents a chain of process-process communications enabling the flow of Data.

label: dataPathTo
comment: The DataPath represents a chain of process-process communications enabling the use of data represented by the Data Access asset.

label: dataPathVisits
comment: Link from a DataPath to each Process visited by the path, including the two processes at the end of the path.

label: extendsDC
comment: The first Data Channel is an extension of the second.

label: extendsDP
comment: The first DataPath is an extension of the second.

label: extendsFwdFlow
comment: Relationship between two data channels indicating that the first carries a data flow to a transparent data relay, and the second carries the same data from the relay further back along the same data path.

label: extendsRevFlow
comment: Relationship between two data channels indicating that the first carries a data flow to a transparent data relay, and the second carries the same data from the relay further along the same data path.

label: flowsFromDP
comment: Link from a Data Flow to the longer DataPath to the source or destination processes. If the flow is in the forward direction, this will be the Data Path to the source process, while if it is a reverse flow, it will be the Data Path to the destination process.

label: flowsToDP
comment: Link from a Data Flow to the shorter DataPath to the source or destination processes. If the flow is in the forward direction, this will be the Data Path to the destination process, while if it is a reverse flow, it will be the Data Path to the source process.

label: flowsViaProcess
comment: Relationship from a DataFlow to the source, destination and other processes between the two via which the data flows.

label: fromProc
comment: The DataPath represents a chain of process-process communications enabling the use of data needed by the Process.

label: fwdPath
comment: Signifies that the data usage involves a flow of data forwards along the data path.

label: fwdRelay
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate Data Access assets that are acting as transparent relays, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isDest
comment: Signifies that the Data Access asset is a destination for the related Data.

label: isPool
comment: Signifies that the Data Access asset is a source and may be a destination for the related Data.

label: isSource
comment: Signifies that the Data Access asset is a source of the related Data.

label: needsField
comment: Relationship from a Data Copy or Data Flow (a serialized data asset) to DataFields denoting that a Process consumes the Data Asset and does not ignore the field. This is a construction state asset used to tag the need for a field, prior to recursively deducing where it can be obtained.

label: possDataDest
comment: Relationship to a potential data destination from another data access asset that may be a (local) source of the data.

label: possRevPath
comment: Signifies that the data usage may involve a flow of data backwards along the data path.

label: relaysAccess
comment: Link from a process on a data path that is being tried as a member of a data channel to the data access for that channel.

label: revPath
comment: Signifies that the data usage involves a flow of data backwards along the data path.

label: revRelay
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate Data Access assets that are acting as transparent relays, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: toProc
comment: The DataPath represents a chain of process-process communications enabling the use of data obtained from the Process.

label: usesDataPath
comment: Relationship between a data flow and a data path.

label: accessesField
comment: Inferred relationship from a Process asset to a Data Field indicating that the Process does not ignore the Data Field. Used to provide a negation of the ignoresField relationship, allowing non-unique nodes to be matched that are used by the Process.

label: containsField
comment: Relationship from a Data asset to DataFields representing distinct data subsets or elements.

label: ignoresField
comment: Relationship from a Process asset to a DataField indicating that although the Process processes certain Data, it does not need the indicated Field. This means the Field can be obscured, e.g., by encryption with a distinct key, or redacted in serialised copies of the data touched by the Process.

label: amends
comment: The Process uses and alters the value of the control settings for the Controller, and is not blocked if it cannot access these settings.

label: amends
comment: The Process initiates reading the Sensor, providing control settings as input and receiving sensed data as output. The Process is not blocked if it cannot access the Sensor.

label: controlsSensor
comment: The Process uses and alters the value of the control settings for the Controller, and is not blocked if it cannot access these settings.

label: controlsThing
comment: Relationship from control input Data to a Thing whose physical actuator or measurement hardware is controlled or configured by the Data.

label: polls
comment: The Process initiates reading the Sensor, receiving sensed data as output. The Process is not blocked if it cannot access the Sensor.

label: reads
comment: The Process initiates reading the Sensor, receiving sensed data as output. The Process is blocked if it cannot access the Sensor.

label: receives
comment: The Sensor sends readings to the Process, and neither end is blocked should this not be possible.

label: senses
comment: Relationship from an IoT Sensor to Data produced by its measurement hardware.

label: updates
comment: The Process uses and alters the value of the control settings for the Controller, and is blocked if it cannot access these settings.

label: updates
comment: The Process initiates reading the Sensor, providing control settings as input and receiving sensed data as output. The Process is blocked if it cannot access the Sensor.

label: hasController
comment: The Stakeholder is legally responsible for use of the Data to the data subject and data regulator.

label: responsibleFor
comment: The Stakeholder is legally responsible for regulating access to Data by a Process.

label: subjectTo
comment: An asset is regulated by the laws of the Jurisdiction.

label: pairsViaBluetooth
comment: The first physical Host is a Bluetooth device, connected via a radio Bluetooth connection to its Bluetooth host.

label: pairsViaUSB
comment: The first physical Host is a USB device, connected via a physical USB connection to its USB host.

label: above
comment: Indicates that one host is provisioned (directly or indirectly) on another.

label: accessesService
comment: A base relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client initiates communication with the service.

label: accessibleFrom
comment: Relationship between a network Subnet and a Space from which that Subnet can be accessed.

label: accessTo
comment: Refers from an access context to the asset (host or process) that can be accessed in that context.

label: accessVia
comment: Refers from an access context to a logical subnet which is connected in that context and may have been the means of access.

label: connectedTo
comment: The Host or Data Centre can send and receive messages on the related LogicalSubnet.

label: controls
comment: The Process provides a means to control and administer user access to the related Host, Process or LogicalSubnet. Where a login shell controls access, it means the user must login to run the controlled process or use admin rights on the controlled host.

label: hasCLI
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate processes in the Console Process class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: hasEmail
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate Human assets with access to email, so modelling error threat patterns can check where this is not the case.

label: hasPhysicalHost
comment: The first Host is a virtual host that is running on the second Host.

label: hosts
comment: The Process is running on the Host.

label: impersonalDevice
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts that have more than one user, so they can be excluded from matching patterns designed to find only personal devices.

label: implements
comment: Relationship from a logical subnet to an abstract subnet indicating that the former provides (part of) the concrete implementation of the latter.

label: implements
comment: Relationship from a WiFi subnet to a WiFi hotspot provided by a mobile device, indicating that the former implements the latter in a specific location.

label: indirectAuthZ
comment: A relationship indicating that a client directly or indirectly communicates with a service, and the client sends an access token on some kind, via intermediaries if necessary, expressing their rights to use back-end resources.

label: interactsRemotelyWith
comment: The Human is an interactive user of the related Process, which they may be accessing via the shell using remote access to the process host.

label: interactsWith
comment: The Human is an interactive user of the related Host or Process, accessing it via the Host user interface (e.g. console). Note that this is a special case of interactsRemotelyWith, which includes this and also remote access by the Human to the Process.

label: isAbstractSubnet
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate subnets that represent (and are implemented by) more complex networks, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns as appropriate.

label: isCluster
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts that represent clusters of hosts, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isHostLAN
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate logical subnets in the HostLAN class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isHotspot
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate WiFiLAN networks that represent mobile hotspots, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns as appropriate.

label: isInternet
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate logical subnets in the Internet class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isLnS
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate processes in the Remote Access Service class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isLocalSubnet
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate subnets that are local to a specific host or group of hosts, so they can be included or excluded in patterns used to determine network accessibility, as appropriate.

label: isMHC
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts in the MobileClient class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isPersonalDevice
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate personal hosts with exactly one user, so so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isRouter
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts in the Router class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: isTrivial
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate some types of simple processes as trivial, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: locatedIn
comment: The physical Host is located in the Space.

label: manages
comment: The Human manages (administers and configures) the related Process (Service), Host and otherwise unmanaged processes running on it, or otherwise unmanaged hosts in a Space.

label: mayBeIn
comment: The physical host may be located in the Space, which means either (a) it is supposed to be there at least some of the time, or (b) it could be advantages for an attacker to steal the host and take it there.

label: operates
comment: The Stakeholder is the legal entity responsible for managing the Host, Process or Private Space (usually but not always a Data Centre).

label: propagatesTo
comment: Relationship from a (host or process) location access context to a process access context indicating that access in the destination context is possible via the host when connected to the system. Used to prevent rights propagating to contexts that can only be used if a process host has first been removed from the system (e.g. stolen).

label: providedBy
comment: The Host or DataCentre provides the means of communication supporting the Network (an Abstract or Logical Subnet), including network allocation and address translation for routing to other connected subnets, and support for EAP authentication mechanisms if appropriate.

label: resourcedBy
comment: The Physical Host is located in the Data Centre, and its resources are managed by the Data Centre.

label: uses
comment: A relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client initiates communication with the service, for application purposes.

label: usesForAuth
comment: A relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client initiates communication with the service, not for application purposes but in order to authenticate itself.

label: usesForAuthZ
comment: A relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client initiates communication with the service, not for application purposes but in order to verify the access rights of a third party.

label: usesIndirectly
comment: An inferred relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client could communicate with the service, but would do so via at least one intermediary.

label: usesRemotely
comment: An inferred relationship created between a client and a service where access can support client user interaction with the service even where the service runs on a remote host from the user.

label: usesService
comment: A base relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client initiates communication with the service, for application purposes or to authenticate itself.

label: usesViaDeputy
comment: An inferred relationship from a client process to a service process indicating that the client could communicate with the service via at least one intermediary.

label: blockedPath
comment: Self-referential relationship used to mark network communication paths that exist, but are blocked by default.

label: blockedSegment
comment: Self-referential relationship used to mark communication routes through gateways (segments) that exist, but are blocked by default.

label: connectsFrom
comment: The Interface provides a connection to some Logical Subnet from the Host.

label: connectsTo
comment: The Interface provides a connection to the Logical Subnet from some Host.

label: end
comment: The NetworkPath finishes at the LogicalSubnet.

label: from
comment: The LogicalSegment routes messages from the LogicalSubnet or Interface.

label: start
comment: The NetworkPath starts at the LogicalSubnet.

label: to
comment: The LogicalSegment routes messages to the LogicalSubnet or Interface.

label: traverses
comment: The NetworkPath traverses a LogicalSegment from one LogicalSubnet to another.

label: via
comment: The LogicalSegment routes messages across Interfaces or through a Host.

label: visits
comment: The Network Path passes through the Logical Subnet, which is either at the start or end of the path, or between the start and end of the path.

label: visitsGateway
comment: The NetworkPath goes from one subnet to another via the host.

label: extends
comment: The first NetworkPath is a longer path consisting of a step from the starting subnet followed by the second path from that subnet.

label: pEndsAt
comment: The path terminating at the NPE/PPE terminator goes to the LogicalSubnet.

label: pVia
comment: The path terminating at the NPE/PPE terminator goes via the LogicalSubnet.

label: runsIn
comment: Link from a process to an context where it needs to execute.

label: usesViaRAS
comment: Inferred link between a client and a service that encodes the fact that the client access the service via a login or remote desktop shell on the service host.

label: accessibleVia
comment: The first Space is inside or adjacent to and can be entered from the second Space.

label: canAccess
comment: The Human (acting in a specific system role) needs and has the right to enter the Space.

label: controlledBy
comment: Access to the Space is decided by the Stakeholder.

label: isWorld
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate the global public space, so it can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: relatesTo
comment: A relationship between a personal (including IoT) device and a Human user. Data on the device may be Personally identifiable information (PII) related to that user.

label: accessFromClient
comment: Refers from a process network access context for a client to a related channel or path to a service indicating that the channel or path can be accessed by the client in this context.

label: accessInterrupted
comment: Indicates that when a client is in a context, access to the service is impossible or may be interrupted.

label: accessToService
comment: Refers from an access context for a service (or host if the service is a login service) to a related channel or path to the service indicating that the service is accessible via that channel or path in this context.

label: accessUninterrupted
comment: From a client context, indicates that when a client is in that context, access to the service is may not be interrupted by the service moving from its context.

label: attackPathFrom
comment: Relates a closed AttackPath from a subnet not used by any client to a NetworkPath from its source into a channel that is used by a client.

label: attackPathVia
comment: Relates an AttackPath from a client towards a service to a composite AttackPath aggregating all such paths towards the service.

label: channelFrom
comment: The ConnectionAsset represents a view of inter-process communication in which the related Process is acting as a Client.

label: channelTo
comment: The ConnectionAsset represents a view of inter-process communication in which the related Process is acting as a Service.

label: channelVia
comment: The ServiceChannel represents a communication channel from a client to a service that uses the related NetworkPath, Hosts, Subnets and Interfaces.

label: controlsChannel
comment: Relationship between client-service channels indicating that authentication and access via the source channel controls authentication via the target channel.

label: flowsViaChannel
comment: Links a data flow to a client-service trust or communication channel on which it depends.

label: flowsViaCS
comment: Links a data flow via a client and thence its service to the client-service trust relationship on which it depends.

label: flowsViaSC
comment: Links a data flow via a service and thence its client to the client-service trust relationship on which it depends.

label: fromInterface
comment: The inter-process communication path or channel goes from a Host to a Subnet via the interface.

label: fromSubnet
comment: The inter-path communication path or channel starts from the LogicalSubnet.

label: isProxy
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate processes in the Service Proxy class (i.e. a reverse proxy), so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: lastInterface
comment: The interface whose address is the source address of messages reaching a service.

label: noAuthN
comment: An inferred relationship from a client to a service indicating that the service does not authenticate the client, but delegates to a separate authentication service.

label: proxyAuthN
comment: An inferred relationship from a client to a service indicating that the service does not authenticate the client, in the special case where at least one of them is an authentication proxy forwarding credentials from clients to back end services for authentication.

label: sharesCredentials
comment: Relationship of a client and service where the client is sharing credentials with the service or from its own client. In the former case, the service uses credentials from the client to access other resources. In the latter, the client is using credentials from its client to access the service.

label: toInterface
comment: The inter-process communication path or channel goes from a Subnet to a Host via the interface.

label: usesAsProxy
comment: Inferred relationship indicating that either the client or the service is a reverse proxy, i.e., either the client is forwarding a request from its client, or the service will be forwarding the request from the client.

label: usesLogicalRoute
comment: The client-service communication path or channel traverses a LogicalSegment from one LogicalSubnet to another.

label: usesViaProxy
comment: An inferred relationship between a client and service indicating that the client could communicate indirectly with the service via at least one reverse proxy, i.e., a process that forwards requests to back-end services.

label: validatesChannel
comment: Relationship between client-service channels indicating that authorization tokens sent via the target channel are validated by exchange with the service via the source channel.

label: viaInterface
comment: Means the communication channel depends on the interface.

label: viaProxy
comment: Inferred relationship which is a base type for both usesAsProxy (direct use of or by a proxy) and usesViaProxy (indirect use). This means it will exist from a client to any service accessed via at least one proxy, and to each of the proxies.

label: viaSharedCredentials
comment: An inferred relationship between two processes indicating that the client could communicate indirectly with the service via credential sharing intermediaries. This means credentials from the client (which may or may not be their own) are sent to the service, which may or may not use them to authenticate the client.

label: viaSubnet
comment: The client-service path or channel passes through the Logical Subnet.

label: fromSpace
comment: Used to save information about client locations from which a service channel is accessible. Used in the construction sequence to prevent constraints intended to suppress spurious channels from working when in a different location context.

label: pathTo
comment: Indicates that a network path leads to a subnet on a service channel.

label: sourceDirect
comment: Relates a Service Channel with a Logical Subnet from which client source addresses are not rewritten by NAT on the way to the service, and hence they can be distinguished from source addresses on that subnet used by attackers.

label: sourceViaNAT
comment: Relates a Service Channel with a Logical Subnet from which client source addresses are rewritten by NAT, and hence cannot be distinguished from source addresses on that subnet used by attackers.

label: toSpace
comment: Used to save information about service locations where the service is accessible via a service channel. Used in the construction sequence to prevent constraints intended to suppress spurious channels from working when in a different location context.

label: isAdult
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate humans in the Adult class, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: worksFor
comment: The Human (acting in a specific system role) is working for and/or subject to instructions from another Stakeholder.

label: fromPhysicalHost
comment: Links a virtual communication channel to a physical host where the channel starts (i.e. where a process is sending messages over a virtual subnet supported by the physical host and/or its physical subnet connections).

label: fromPhysicalInterface
comment: The virtual communication path or channel goes from a Host to a Subnet via the interface.

label: isScalable
comment: Self-referential relationship used to designate hosts that are replicable, so they can be included or excluded in matching patterns on base classes as appropriate.

label: managedBy
comment: Relationship between a Virtual Host and the Data Centre by which it is provisioned. Signifies that the Data Centre allocates resources and may provide other services as part of a management platform such as K8s.

label: overlays
comment: Relationship between a (virtual) network implemented as an IP address overlay using iptables at participating hosts and the network(s) providing the necessary communication between those hosts.

label: provisionedBy
comment: The VirtualHost is provisioned using a related physical Host.

label: toPhysicalHost
comment: Links a virtual communication channel to a physical host where the channel ends  (i.e. where a process is receiving messages over a virtual subnet supported by the physical host and/or its physical subnet connections).

label: toPhysicalInterface
comment: The virtual communication path or channel goes from a Subnet to a Host via the interface.

label: usesPhysicalRoute
comment: The virtual communication path or channel traverses a LogicalSegment from one LogicalSubnet to another.

label: usesPhysicalSubnet
comment: Relates a virtual subnet and a physical subnet on which the virtual subnet depends.

label: viaHostChannel
comment: Link from a virtual channel (an infrastructure requirement to support communication via a virtual subnet) and a host channel (representing infrastructure capability to route messages via a physical network path between physical hosts supporting the virtual communication endpoints).

label: viaPhysicalSubnet
comment: The virtualised communication path or channel depends on the underlying (usually physical) Subnet.

label: viaVirtualChannel
comment: Link from a comms channel or a virtual subnet (both representing application level communication paths or connections) to a virtual channel (which represents an infrastructure level communication requirement to support a virtual network).

label: viaPhysicalPath
comment: Communication between two physical hosts on the host path uses the related physical network path.
